I have been using Dropbox for nearly 15 years and have referred many yet am sad to say they have some of the least helpful, or frankly non-existent, options in the case of a security breach of any kind. I feel ill-supported and uncomfortable keeping even my personal email or basic contact info linked to my account at this time.  They alert you saying a new login has occurred on an unfamiliar device, to include their location and IP address, yet they do not allow you to remove all connected devices or alter privacy or access of already connected computers even after changing your password. In addition, there is no security protocol in place that can help you once another has logged in, aside from writing their help center and waiting 2-3 business days while your account is compromised.  All it would take is a simple button, as programs and personal accounts of all kinds have these days, that would log out all devices to ensure security.
